# Project 2: Ultra Pay Recurring Payment Support on Private Channels
An Ajax merchant should be able to register recurring payment mandates and present payment requests using those mandates using Payment Accounts associated with Private Channels in the Payer Ajax (PSP) Wallet.
Practically, this translates to support for recurring payments on Zapp Account, Pixel Accounts, Pay Later Accounts, and now the Jazz Savings Acconts through Ultra Pay (Pay with Payzapp)

## Private Channel Recurring Payments Support in Ajax 
- Ajax - Mandates (Acquiring PSP recurring payment tokens) {if payment account in the ajax psp wallet is account-based rather than form-factor based, we don't need to introduce issuer-side mandates}
- Ajax Support Panel - Mandates, Payment Accounts management
- Ajax Payment Acceptance Product enhancements to support Auto-pay Support
- Ajax Recurring Payment Support on Closed-loop Payment Instruments (Athena Private Channels)
- Ultra Pay interface for Recurring Payments (In-app UI)

